This can be seen as having grave consequences when, for example, a student sends an informal or unclear email to a professor about a crucial academic issue. An example could be if the student was to send an email which did not have a proper subject heading and used too casual an address or manner, or simply did not elaborate clearly the information the professor would need to process their query. The student could have missed deadlines, gained negative marks or failed to receive any form of help by not being as clear.

This problem can easily be prevented as the student could have made sure to use proper email etiquette, with a clear subject, polite manner of address, appropriate introduction and conclusion, stating the point of the email precisely so as to avoid misinterpretation.
